E AND R AMENDMENTS TO LB 1126
Introduced by Guereca, 7, Chairman Enrollment and Review
1 1. Strike the original sections and all amendments thereto and
2 insert the following new sections:
3 Section 1. Sections 1 to 39 of this act shall be known and may be
4 cited as the Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act.
5 Sec. 2. The purpose of the Infrastructure Development Investment
6 Program Act is to assist in financing qualified projects by providing
7 loans and other forms of financial assistance to eligible entities for
8 the construction, improvement, or enhancement of transportation
9 infrastructure that is necessary for public purposes.
10 Sec. 3. For purposes of the Infrastructure Development Investment
11 Program Act:
12 (1) Capitalization means the aggregate of all funds deposited in the
13 investment program from any federal, state, local, or private source,
14 including, but not limited to, any transfer, grant, loan, loan repayment,
15 investment earning, and bond proceed;
16 (2) Commission means the State Highway Commission;
17 (3) Contracting agency has the same meaning as in section 39-2802;
18 (4) Department means the Department of Transportation or any
19 successor agency designated to implement and administer the
20 Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act;
21 (5) Eligible cost means:
22 (a) For any project that is federally funded, any cost permitted
23 under an applicable federal statute, regulation, or guidance document
24 that governs state infrastructure banks, transportation credit programs,
25 or revolving loan funds;
26 (b) For any project that is funded by this state or a political
27 subdivision of this state, any cost, including, but not limited to, the
-1-

