LB1126 LB1126
MJP - 03/25/2026 MJP - 03/25/2026
1 cost for any: Preliminary engineering; traffic, revenue, or environmental
2 study; right-of-way acquisition; legal, financial, and technical
3 consulting service; construction or construction management; project
4 facility; equipment; or nonoperating cost that is necessary for the
5 completion of an eligible project; or
6 (c) For any project that is a hybrid or multi-sector project, any
7 cost approved by the commission, including any intermodal or utility-
8 related infrastructure that is necessary for project integration;
9 (6)(a) Eligible entity means any:
10 (i) Political subdivision;
11 (ii) Contracting agency; or
12 (iii) Private partner engaged in a public-private partnership as
13 defined in section 39-2802.
14 (b) Eligible entity includes any combination of two or more such
15 political subdivisions or private partners, acting jointly to finance,
16 construct, own, or operate an eligible project;
17 (7)(a) Eligible project means any transportation infrastructure
18 project that provides any of the following public benefits:
19 (i) Accelerating the delivery of transportation improvements;
20 (ii) Enhancing the mobility or safety of people in this state;
21 (iii) Enhancing the economy of this state;
22 (iv) Promoting economic development in this state; or
23 (v) Improving the quality of life of the general public.
24 (b) Eligible project includes, but is not limited to, any highway,
25 street, road, bridge, transit system, rail facility, airport, port, and
26 bicycle or pedestrian facility;
27 (8) Financial assistance includes, but is not limited to, any loan,
28 credit enhancement, capital or debt service reserve, interest rate
29 subsidy, provision of letter of credit, line of credit, and guarantee,
30 and any other lawful financing mechanism that is approved by the
31 commission and, where applicable, is consistent with federal and state
-2-

ER159 ER159
LB1126 LB1126
MJP - 03/25/2026 MJP - 03/25/2026
1 law;
2 (9)(a) Financing agreement means any contract or instrument executed
3 between the investment program and an eligible entity for a loan or
4 financial assistance.
5 (b) Financing agreement includes, but is not limited to, any loan
6 agreement, trust indenture, security or reimbursement agreement,
7 guarantee agreement, and resolution, and any similar instrument that is
8 approved by the commission that contains loan terms and repayment
9 provisions;
10 (10) Investment program means the infrastructure development
11 investment program created under section 4 of this act; and
12 (11) Political subdivision has the same meaning as in section
13 39-2802.
14 Sec. 4. (1) The infrastructure development investment program is
15 created and shall be housed within the department for administrative
16 purposes.
17 (2) The commission shall administer the investment program, with
18 administrative and operational support from the department. The
19 department shall provide the commission with the necessary personnel to
20 manage the day-to-day operations of the investment program.
21 (3) The commission is the final authority for selecting projects to
22 receive financial assistance from the investment program.
23 Sec. 5. (1) The commission shall:
24 (a) Adopt bylaws, policies, and operating procedures that govern the
25 administration of the investment program;
26 (b) Approve or deny applications for financial assistance based on
27 established evaluation criteria;
28 (c) Establish financial, risk management, and internal control
29 policies consistent with generally accepted accounting principles; and
30 (d) Approve annual budgets, audits, and reports for the investment
31 program.
-3-

