MJP - 03/25/2026 MJP - 03/25/2026
1 (2) The commission may:
2 (a) Enter into any cooperative agreement with any federal or state
3 agency, local government, or private entity; and
4 (b) Delegate any administrative or technical function to any
5 personnel or agent of the commission as necessary to implement the
6 Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act.
7 Sec. 6. The commission may establish an advisory committee that is
8 comprised of representatives from eligible entities, metropolitan
9 planning organizations, and the private sector for the purpose of
10 providing guidance on project prioritization, credit policy, or
11 compliance matters.
12 Sec. 7. (1) The Infrastructure Development Investment Program Fund
13 is created. The commission shall administer the fund. The fund shall
14 consist of any:
15 (a) Transfer authorized by the Legislature;
16 (b) Federal money, including, but not limited to, any loan, grant,
17 or cooperative agreement proceeds;
18 (c) State or local grant;
19 (d) Contribution, donation, endowment, or grant from any public or
20 private source;
21 (e) Repayment, interest, or fee, or other income generated by
22 investment program assistance;
23 (f) Bond proceeds or other financing proceeds; and
24 (g) Lawful source that is approved by the commission.
25 (2) Money in the fund may be used by the commission for any purpose
26 that is described in section 8 of this act.
27 (3) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
28 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
29 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
30 (4) All repayments of money provided from the fund and all
31 investment earnings from money in the fund shall be credited to the fund.
-4-

