MJP - 03/25/2026 MJP - 03/25/2026
1 (8) The ability for the applicant to repay the financial assistance
2 according to the established terms and conditions.
3 Sec. 22. The investment program shall cause an annual independent
4 audit of all financial activities, including loan portfolios, investment
5 earnings, debt obligations, and fund transfers. The audit shall be
6 performed by a certified public accounting firm in accordance with
7 generally accepted government auditing standards.
8 Sec. 23. (1) The investment program shall prepare and
9 electronically submit a report to the Clerk of the Legislature no later
10 than November 1 of each year. The report shall include the following
11 information relating to the investment program:
12 (a) A statement of financial position and changes in net assets;
13 (b) A summary of lending and investment activities for each account
14 and eligible project;
15 (c) A list of each project that is financed, including the borrower,
16 purpose, loan terms, and repayment status; and
17 (d) Administrative and operating costs, fees collected, and reserve
18 balances.
19 (2) Each such report shall be published and made publicly available
20 on the website for the investment program.
21 Sec. 24. The investment program shall operate in compliance with:
22 (1) Federal law and program guidance applicable to state
23 infrastructure banks, including capitalization, use-of-funds, and
24 reporting requirements established under 23 U.S.C. 610, or any other
25 applicable federal law, as such federal law existed on January 1, 2026;
26 (2) State fiscal and procurement laws, except where specific
27 exemptions are provided under the Infrastructure Development Investment
28 Program Act; and
29 (3) Any cooperative agreements entered into with the United States
30 Department of Transportation and its operating administrations or other
31 federal agencies.
