1 Sec. 25. The investment program is authorized to issue revenue
2 bonds, notes, or other evidence of indebtedness for the purposes of
3 financing, refinancing, or refunding loans and other eligible costs under
4 the Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act. Obligations may be
5 issued in any amount and at any time as approved by the commission to
6 meet the funding needs of any approved project. The issuance of bonds
7 under the Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act is separate
8 and distinct from any authority or limitation to issue bonds under the
9 Nebraska Highway Bond Act.
10 Sec. 26. (1) Each obligation that is issued by the investment
11 program shall be a special, limited obligation that is payable solely
12 from revenue, repayments, pledged receipts, or other legally available
13 funds of the investment program, and shall not constitute a general
14 obligation of the State of Nebraska or a pledge of the full faith and
15 credit of the State of Nebraska.
16 (2) Each obligation shall bear a clear statement on its face that
17 such obligation is a special, limited obligation that is payable solely
18 from revenue, repayments, pledged receipts, or other legally available
19 funds of the investment program, and shall not constitute a general
20 obligation of the State of Nebraska or a pledge of the full faith and
21 credit of the State of Nebraska.
22 (3) The holder of an obligation shall not have the right to compel
23 the levy of any tax or compel any appropriation by the State of Nebraska
24 for the payment of debt service.
25 Sec. 27. (1) The investment program shall maintain a debt service
26 coverage ratio consistent with prudent fiscal standards and bond
27 covenants.
28 (2) No obligation shall be issued that would cause the debt or
29 liability of the investment program to exceed available pledged revenue.
30 Sec. 28. (1) Prior to issuance, an obligation shall be authorized
31 by a resolution of the commission specifying the principal amount,
