4 designated issuing authority.
5 (3) Bond proceedings may include:
6 (a) A trust indenture or similar agreement that establishes pledges
7 of revenue, covenants, reserve requirements, and flow-of-funds
8 structures;
9 (b) Authorization for refunding or advance refunding;
10 (c) Creation of special funds and reserve accounts; and
11 (d) Appointment of trustees, paying agents, and financial advisors
12 as needed.
13 Sec. 29. (1) The investment program may pledge any repayment,
14 investment earning, or interest subsidy, or any other investment program
15 income to the payment of any obligation or related reserve.
16 (2) Each such pledge shall constitute a valid and binding lien upon
17 the pledged revenue from the time of the pledge, without the need for
18 physical delivery, filing, or recording.
19 (3) Each such lien shall be valid and enforceable against any party
20 having a claim of any kind against the investment program, whether or not
21 such party has notice of the lien.
22 Sec. 30. (1) Any obligation may be sold at public or private sale,
23 as determined by the commission, at any price and interest rate deemed to
24 be in the best interest of the investment program.
25 (2) Each obligation shall be executed on behalf of the investment
26 program by the officer authorized pursuant to rules and regulations that
27 are adopted and promulgated by the commission.
28 (3) Each such obligation may bear a facsimile seal and signature,
29 which remain valid even if the officer ceases to hold office prior to
