1 refunding obligation to retire outstanding debt, reduce debt service,
2 restructure any maturity, or achieve savings. Any such refunding shall
3 not extend any final maturity beyond the useful life of the financed
4 asset.
5 Sec. 32. (1) The investment program shall maintain a bond service
6 account and such reserve accounts as required by bond proceedings.
7 (2) Debt service payments from pledged revenue or other legally
8 available money that are remitted to the State Treasurer shall be
9 credited by the State Treasurer to the Infrastructure Development
