15 Sec. 33. An obligation that is issued under the Infrastructure
16 Development Investment Program Act, the transfer of such obligation, and
17 the income from such issuance and transfer, including the profit from the
18 sale of such obligation, shall be exempt from state and local taxation.
19 Sec. 34. An obligation that is issued under the Infrastructure
20 Development Investment Program Act shall be a lawful investment for any
21 bank, trust company, insurance company, pension fund, or other fiduciary
22 and may be accepted as security for the deposit of public money.
23 Sec. 35. Each obligation shall be issued in conformity with the
24 Infrastructure Development Investment Program Act and federal securities
25 regulations, including continuing disclosure requirements and limitations
26 on arbitrage earnings under 26 U.S.C. 148, as such section existed on
27 January 1, 2026.
28 Sec. 36. (1) In the event of default, any bondholder or trustee may
