3 Sec. 37. (1) The commission may adopt and promulgate rules and
4 regulations to carry out the Infrastructure Development Investment
5 Program Act.
6 (2) No later than July 1, 2027, the commission shall adopt and
7 promulgate rules and regulations to provide for:
8 (a) The transparent, equitable, and nondiscriminatory administration
9 of financial assistance;
10 (b) Public oversight and consistent scoring criteria for
11 applications and project evaluations;
12 (c) Systems to track compliance, defaults, and repayments;
13 (d) Prompt corrective actions to address any audit finding or
14 material weakness;
15 (e) Administration of the Infrastructure Development Investment
16 Program Act and response to evolving best practices in infrastructure
17 finance and management; and
18 (f) Application procedures, loan evaluation, pricing standards,
19 credit ratings, and ongoing monitoring to protect the integrity of the
20 portfolio of the investment program and ensure access across
21 jurisdictions.
22 Sec. 38. (1) The commission shall adopt and maintain internal
23 control policies, investment standards, and risk management frameworks to
24 ensure prudent fiscal operations.
25 (2) Such controls shall comply with applicable state auditing,
26 ethics, and administrative procedures.
27 Sec. 39. The investment program shall maintain a website for access
