5 (b) Make or give any undue or unreasonable preference or advantage
6 to any particular person;
7 (c) Subject any type of traffic to any undue or unreasonable
8 prejudice, delay, or disadvantage in any respect whatsoever;
9 (d) Charge or receive any greater compensation in the aggregate for
10 the transportation of a like kind of property or passengers for a shorter
11 than for a longer distance over the same line or route, except as the
12 commission may prescribe in special cases to prevent manifest injuries,
13 except that no manifest injustice shall be imposed upon any person at
14 intermediate points. This section shall not prevent the commission from
15 making group or emergency rates;
16 (e) Demand, charge, or collect, by any device whatsoever, a lesser
17 or greater compensation for any service rendered than that filed with or
18 prescribed by the commission; or
19 (f) Change any rate, schedule, or classification in any manner
20 whatsoever before application has been made to the commission and
21 permission granted for that purpose, except as otherwise provided in
22 section 86-155.
23 (2) This section shall not prohibit any common carrier from, and a
24 common carrier shall not be subject to any fine, penalty, or forfeiture
25 for, performing services free or at reduced rates to:
26 (a) The United States, the State of Nebraska, or any governmental
27 subdivision thereof;
28 (b) The employees, both present and retired, of such common carrier;
29 (c) Any person when the object is to provide relief in case of any
30 disaster;
31 (d) Any person who transports property for charitable purposes;
