13 meeting, or will meet, the proposed need for the proposed service and (b)
14 (2) that even if the applicant's service will be responsive to a public
15 demand or need, the that applicant would not be able to serve such this
16 need in a specified manner without endangering or impairing the
17 operations of existing carriers contrary to the public interest.
18 (2)(a) No transportation network company or participating driver
19 shall engage in intrastate medicaid nonemergency medical transportation
20 services unless such transportation network company or participating
21 driver holds a license to engage in such services under subsection (4) of
22 section 75-311.
23 (b) Subsection (1) of this section does not apply to a
24 transportation network company or participating driver that holds a
25 license under subsection (4) of section 75-311.
